The paper deals with the synthesis of RGB frames from event cameras, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method is based on deep learning, which suggests that it could also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of recurrent modules, which are commonly used in neural networks for sequence modeling, indicating a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
